records.addlTxt:
9:03 AM Defendant Cole Q. Carroll in court. Attorney Elizabeth F Svehlek in court for Cole Q. Carroll. Prosecuting attorney Mary M Sowinski Ms. in court for the State of Wisconsin. Calling 21CF346, 22CF131, 22CM69, 22TR1045, 22TR1048 & 22TR1049. Sowinski states no motion has been filed. Judge states has represented Defendant in the past - questions Defendant. Defendant states he would like her to preside. Sowinski states will orally argue - Defendant has sought out treatment - will take into account - does not believe joinder will be contested - there may be a resolution. Svehlek does not object. Court grants motion for joinder for all 3 cases. Sowinski has complied with victim rights. Bond continued. adj. 09:14 AM
Pre-trial conference scheduled for December 13, 2022 at 09:30 am.
Jury trial scheduled for May 4, 2023 at 08:30 am.

Calling 21CF346, 22CF131, 22CM69, 22TR1045, 22TR1048 & 22TR1049. Svehlek states there will be motion for cases to be tied for trial - would like to set for motion hearing. Bond continued. Defendant to appear in person at next hearing. adj. 02:38 PM
Motion hearing scheduled for October 14, 2022 at 09:00 am.

records.addlTxt:
10:26 AM Prosecuting attorney Mary M Sowinski in court for the State of Wisconsin. Defendant Cole Q. Carroll in court. Attorney Elizabeth F Svehlek in court for Cole Q. Carroll. Calling 22CF131, 21CF346 & 22CM69. 22CF131 set for a preliminary hearing. State calls Oneida County Sheriffs Sergeant Brian Keller/sworn/direct by Sowinski/witness identifies Defendant/continued direct by Sowinski/Sowinski would like judicial notice of Defendant's bonds in other cases/Svehlek objects/Court directs Sowinski to ask further questions/continued direct by Sowinski/would like adjournment to provide certified copies of bond/cross by Svehlek/redirect by Sowinski/Court questions Defendant/re-cross by Svehlek/Court questions Defendant/witness is excused. Svehlek/Sowinski statement to probable cause. Court finds probable cause exists and binds Defendant over. Sowinski states Information will be filed that mirrors Complaint. Svehlek willing to proceed to Arraignment today; waives further reading and enters not guilty pleas. Court does not need certified copies of bond. Sowinski statement to Defendant's traffic cases/global resolution. Court will leave on calendar. Defendant statement to new address - does not know street number Court directs Defendant to find out address and notify COC office. Bond continued. adj. 10:58 AM
Pre-trial conference scheduled for September 13, 2022 at 02:30 pm.
